									<article itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/NewsArticle" id="post-799163" class="post-799163 post post-excerpt hentry track_event"  data-event-tracking="Outfit| 0| Primary – 13 Text 1 Large 6 Small| 0| 1| zon| HP top stories&quot; " >
										<header>	
						<h2 itemprop="name" class="entry-title"><a itemprop="url" href="http://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/squeaky-wheels-website-explains-origins-of-montreals-street-names" target="_self" rel="bookmark" title="">Squeaky Wheels: Ever wondered why your street has that name?</a></h2>					</header>

										<div itemprop="articleBody" class="entry-content">
						Questions and answers about traffic and transit. This week: the origins of Montreal's street names.					</div>
										
					<figure class="thumbnail " ><a id="link-799477" href="http://montrealgazette.com/news/local-news/squeaky-wheels-website-explains-origins-of-montreals-street-names" target="_self"><img itemprop="image" src="http://wpmedia.montrealgazette.com/2016/05/montreal-que-august-27-2014-robert-bourassa-s-wife-a.jpeg?quality=55&#038;strip=all&#038;w=625&#038;h=469&#038;crop=1" 
				class="attachment-post-thumbnail wp-post-image " 
				alt="Robert Bourassa&#039;s wife, Andrée Bourassa, left , is standing with Montreal Mayor Denis Coderre during a ceremony at city hall in 2014. to honour the former premier with a street name. The city of Montreal has had a website since 2007 where residents can peruse the origin of 6,000 street names. The site is available only in French. " 
				width="625" 
				height="469" 
				id="img-799477"/></a></figure>
				
